---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Jakob Neugebauer" activePage="home">
  <div class="home-header">
    <div class="home-header-text">
      <h1 class="home-headline">AI Systems<br />& Data Infrastructure</h1>
      <p class="home-name">Jakob Neugebauer</p>
      <p class="home-role">Independent AI Systems Builder</p>
    </div>
    <div class="home-headshot">
      <img src="/images/headshot.jpg" alt="Jakob Neugebauer" class="home-headshot-img" />
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="home-intro">
    <p>
      Most organizations sit on data they either process manually or don't process at all.
    </p>
    <p>
      Contracts in PDFs, financial filings in legacy formats, regulatory documents across jurisdictions – <strong>valuable information</strong> maintained by someone, somewhere in the organisation, or <strong>never touched in the first place</strong>.
    </p>
    <p>
      I build the pipelines that take over that work. Extraction, classification, structuring, indexing – <strong>end to end, no human in the loop where none is needed</strong>. What used to take a team now runs on its own.
    </p>
    <p>
      The infrastructure depends on the constraints. <strong>Data sensitivity, regulation, and cost</strong> decide whether that means cloud inference, <strong>local models</strong>, or <strong>hybrid setups</strong> that keep sensitive data where it belongs.
    </p>
    <p>
      The model is usually the easy part. The real work is in <strong>validation layers, infrastructure</strong>, and the kind of system design that keeps things predictable once they leave the demo environment.
    </p>
    <p>
      I work best in small teams with short decision cycles – the kind of setup where things actually ship. Based in Vienna, background in Economics (WU Wien), International Management (Bocconi), and Information Systems (FH Technikum Wien, completed while working full-time).
    </p>
    <p>
      I write about some of what I build in the <a href="/notes">Notes</a> section. If any of this sounds relevant, <a href="/lets-talk">let's talk</a>.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="home-links">
    <a href="#" onclick="window.scrollTo({top:0,behavior:'smooth'});return false;">About</a>
    <a href="/notes">Notes</a>
    <a href="/lets-talk">Let's Talk</a>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
